<item>
            <title>[PIG-3031] Update Pig to use a newer version of joda-time</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3031</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The current version is 1.6, which is quite old (~4 years at this point). Is there any reason not to bring us up to a newer version? I tried to compile the 1.6 source and it didn&apos;t work because dependencies are outdated, and so on. Also, the interfaces have matured.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12614870">PIG-3031</key>
            <summary>Update Pig to use a newer version of joda-time</summary>
